  "id": "019cf612-df06-78f0-a61b-dc0301250b20",
  "content": "# M3.4 Graph Edge Improvements — Implementation Plan\n\n> **Status:** Shipped (v0.3.0)\n\n**Goal:** Fix graph edge creation so graph-expanded retrieval produces meaningfully different results from vector-only (currently 0-2 extra results per query → target 5-15).\n\n**Architecture:** Three fixes across two crates. Fix 1 (adapter): `RustModuleMap` resolves `crate::`/`super::` imports to real file paths. Fix 2 (kernel): `MarkdownChunker` extracts code spans, links, and code block references via `pulldown-cmark`. Fix 3 (kernel): `discover_cross_file_relations()` post-processes all chunks to find type/trait definitions and cross-file usages.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust, tree-sitter, pulldown-cmark, corvia-kernel ChunkingPipeline\n\n---\n",
